quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  43,23,"And similarly, We did not send a warner to a town before you, but its affluent people said, 'We have found our fathers on a certain way, and we are following their footprints.""
  43,24,"He said, "Even if I bring to you something better in guidance than that on which you have found your fathers?" They said, 'We totally disbelieve in what you are sent with.""
  43,25,"So, We took revenge from them. Now look, how was the end of those who rejected (Our messengers)."
  43,26,"And (recall) when Ibrahim said to his father and to his people, "I disown that which you worship,"
  43,27,"except the One who has originated me; so He will guide me.""
  43,28,"And he made it a word lasting among his posterity, so that they may return."
  43,29,"But, I gave these and their fathers enjoyment, until the truth came to them, and a messenger who explains (it)."
  43,30,"And when the truth came to them, they said, "This is magic, and we totally disbelieve in it.""
  43,31,"And they say, "Why was this Qur'an not revealed on a great man from (either on the two towns?""
  43,32,"Is it they who distribute the mercy of your Lord? We have distributed among them their livelihood in the worldly life, and have raised some of them over others in ranks, so that some of them may put some others to work. And the mercy of your Lord is much better than what they accumulate."
  43,33,"And were it not that all people will become of a single creed (i.e. disbelief), We will have caused, for the benefit of those who disbelieve in Rahman, roofs of their houses to be made of silver, and the stairs as well, on which they will climb,"